  month = sep,
  publisher = {Zenodo},
  doi = {10.5281/ZENODO.16994544},
  abstract = {Presentation slides from the DraCorOS Training Session ``From Dramatic Text to DraCor TEI: XML/TEI Introduction, Encoding Drama in TEI, and Automation of Encoding'' given at the DraCor Summit in Berlin on 1 September 2025.~~ In the first part of this session, we introduce XML/TEI and discuss why the TEI format is used in Computational Literary Studies. In the second part, we present different workflows to encode dramatic texts in TEI. We consider three types of text sources: texts without any markup, texts with basic markup, and texts with advanced markup. We also discuss how to automate the encoding process and which tools may be used for support. Finally, we provide a flowchart to help you choose a suitable encoding workflow for your project.},
